Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Mix onion, peppers, oil, lime juice and cumin in 13x9-inch baking pan. Mix coating mix and lime peel; use to coat chops as directed on package. Discard any remaining coating mixture. Place chops over vegetable mixture in baking pan. Bake 25 minutes or until chops are cooked through. Remove chops from pan; cut into strips. Spoon pork and vegetable mixture evenly over the tortillas: roll up. Serve topped with TACO BELL HOME ORIGINALS Salsa and BREAKSTONE'S or KNUDSEN Sour Cream, if desired.